# tools/scan_dead_imports.ignore вҖ” known scanner false positives
#
# Populated by `tools/scan_dead_imports.py --write-ignore` AFTER
# a clean run of `tools/prune_unused_imports.py --include-public
# --final-check` confirms the codebase has no truly-removable
# dead imports.  Any name the precise agda-driven tool kept but
# this regex scanner flags is a false positive by definition,
# and belongs here.
#
# Hand-edit to add entries (e.g. a new mixfix operator the scanner
# misclassifies) or remove them when an entry becomes stale (the
# underlying name was genuinely deleted in a later edit).
#
# Format:
#   [path/relative/to/src.agda]
#     name1
#     _вҲ·_
#     mapвӮҒ to mapвӮ‘      вҶҗ renaming-pair from the scanner's output
#
# Names are matched EXACTLY against the scanner's reported text.

